President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation recognizing May 22 as National Maritime Day. The proclamation honors the men and women of the United States Merchant Marine for their contributions to America's economy and national security. It acknowledges their role in equipping military forces at sea during times of conflict and their support for humanitarian missions. The proclamation also highlights the importance of the Merchant Marine in facilitating the safe passage of American goods and strengthening the nation's economy. The President calls upon the people of the United States to observe this day with appropriate activities and encourages all ships sailing under the American flag to dress ship on May 22.